      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "let D = parseInt(readline());\nlet seconds = Math.trunc(D / 1000);\nlet out = [];\n\nlet days = Math.trunc(seconds / 86400);\nif (days >= 1)\n{\n    out.push(days + \"d\");\n    seconds -= 86400 * days;\n}\n\nlet hours = Math.trunc(seconds / 3600);\nif (hours >= 1)\n{\n    out.push(hours + \"h\");\n    seconds -= 3600 * hours;\n}\n\nlet minutes = Math.trunc(seconds / 60);\nif (minutes >= 1)\n{\n    out.push(minutes + \"m\");\n    seconds -= 60 * minutes;\n}\n\nif (seconds >= 1 || out.length === 0)\n{\n    out.push(seconds + \"s\");\n}\n\nprint(out.join(\" \"));",
